method.methdesc:
Visual interpretation of high resolution aerial orthoimagery was done in Arc Map 10.0 for both verification of known FAA ORS points and digitization of newly located wind turbine locations. Sources for wind turbine facilities and turbine specification attribution were numerous and often found in a web search of industry publications and press releases. The list, on a state basis, is available upon request. 
        Sources used: 
        Bing Maps Aerial from ESRI Arc Map Base Maps-updated continually; County Boundaries 2001, http://nationalatlas.gov/atlasftp.html#countyp; 
        Digital Globe most current imagery-Rapid Delivery of Online Geospatial-Intelligence (RDOG) from a National Geospatial Intelligence Agency contract under NextView License-updated continually, https://rdog.digitalglobe.com/myDigitalGlobe/RegistrationRequest.html ; 
        Energy Information Administration (EIA), EIA-860 dataset. http://www.eia.gov; 
        FAA-Digital Obstacle File-https://nfdc.faa.gov/tod/public/TOD_DOF.html-through product release date July 22, 2013; Federal Information Processing Standards-http://www.itl.nist.gov/fipspubs/fip5-2.htm 
        Homeland Security Infrastructure Program (HSIP) 2012 release: https://www.hifldwg.org/public/HSIP%20Gold%20Freedom%20One%20Pager_July%202012.pdf; Industry Press Releases from a web search for turbine and facility information; 
        Industry Turbine Model Specifications from manufacturer found in publicly available website searches; 
        Local Government Permitting Agencies-publicly available website searches, often published environmental site assessments or other permitting for turbines and facilities; 
        National Atlas-http://nationalatlas.gov/atlasftp.html#statep0; 
        Software used:
        ESRI ArcMap 10.0 and 10.1-http://www.esri.com/; USDA NAIP county mosaic orthoimagery from http://datagateway.nrcs.usda.gov/; USGS SDDS orthoimagery from internal USGS EROS data Center Server from http://viewer.nationalmap.gov/example/services.html.  http://basemap.nationalmap.gov/ArcGIS/rest/services/USGSImageryOnly/MapServer - updated continually; Wind Energy Data and Information (WENDI) from Oak Ridge National Laboratory. No longer funded, no longer available, facility data collected through 2012 just prior to de-funding
